<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p>Last updated on: 11/14/2021</p>
<p>This Privacy Policy explains our policies and procedures regarding the collection, use and   sharing of your information when you use our application, and tells you about your privacy rights  and how the law protects you.</p>
<p>As stated in the informed consent form you signed before the study, your physician who will follow you during the study and the institution where the physician works undertake to protect the confidentiality of the information obtained about their patients in a manner that respects personal rights and within the framework of this "Privacy Policy". We carry out all kinds of actions regarding the acquisition, use, storage and sharing of information with other parties in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Law No.6698 and the regulations related to these laws. In this context, we use your personal data to provide you with health services and to improve these services. By using our application, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p>
<p>Patients' information is not shared with third parties, except in cases where the requests and instructions of patients are available within the scope of the relevant legislation. Responsible investigators will inform the relevant patients in this regard, as stipulated in the Law No. 6698, in cases where personal data are seized by malicious and unauthorized persons.</p>
<h1>Collection and Use of Your Personal Data</h1>
<h2>Types of Data Collected</h2>
<h3>Personal Data</h3>
<p>When using our application, we may ask you to provide us with certain personal information that can be used to communicate with or identify you. Personal information may include, but is not limited to:
<ul class="list">
    <li>First name and last name</li>
    <li>Phone number</li>
</ul>
</p>
<h3>Usage Data</h3>
<p>Usage data is collected automatically while using the application. We may automatically collect certain information for troubleshooting purposes, including but not limited to the type of mobile device you use, the unique ID of your mobile device, the IP address of your mobile device, the operating system, and the type of mobile Internet browser you use.</p>
<h3>Information Collected While Using the Application</h3>
<p>While using our application, we may collect the following with your prior consent to provide services to you:
<ul class="list">
    <li><strong>Camera Data</strong>
        <p>
            Used for permissions that are associated with accessing camera or capturing images from the device. This permission allows the application to capture the images of medicine that is used by the user. In addition, by using the camera, the users can capture the images of any documents that they want to send to their doctor. Resulting files are stored in the device and can be sent to a Doktorum Yanımda server.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Microphone Data</strong>
        <p>
            Used for permissions that are associated with accessing microphone and capturing audio using device microphone. This permission allows the application to capture audio when the users want to send each other voice messages. Resulting files are stored in the device and can also be sent to a Doktorum Yanımda server.
        </p>
    </li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
    This information can be uploaded to our servers and / or another institution's server from which we get service. You can enable or disable access to this information at any time in your device settings.
</p>
<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>Our application does not appeal to anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under the age of 13. If you are a parent or guardian and know that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us. If we become aware that we collect personal data from anyone under the age of 13 without parental consent, we will take steps to remove that information from our servers.</p>
<h2>Changes To This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on our application.</p>
<p>We will notify you by email and / or an important notice about the application before the change becomes effective and we update the "Last updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy.</p>
<h2>Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us by e-mail: info@hastaizleme.com</p>
